HEADWORD: Hayrack
<hw>Hay"rack`</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"r⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
frame mounted on the running gear of a wagon, and used in hauling hay,
straw, sheaves, etc.; -- called also <altname>hay rigging</altname> and
<altname>hay rig</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

